overview: The user initiated a request for thorough browser-based testing of the
  sleep questionnaire application. The agent systematically approached this by
  first verifying the dev server status and then navigating the application. Key
  testing areas included the main questionnaire flow, where the agent tested
  both manual input and utilized a "Pre-fill & Jump to Report" development
  feature to quickly reach and test the report generation. During this, the
  agent debugged initial confusion around navigation, clarifying it was likely a
  rendering timing issue. The agent successfully confirmed the PDF download
  functionality. Subsequently, the admin dashboard login was tested, where the
  agent verified the error handling for incorrect passwords after determining
  the  file was protected. Finally, an attempt to test the
   endpoint revealed it requires authentication. The overall
  outcome was a comprehensive validation of core application functionalities and
  error handling.
